| j. Has a stylish and attractive look and design | e. Social approval? |
|------------------------------------------------|---------------------|
| k. Has high-quality food                        | f. Self-respect?     |
summary_markdown: This table presents a comparative structure, juxtaposing desirable product attributes with potential psychological benefits. On one side, it lists tangible features such as a "stylish and attractive look and design" and "high-quality food." These attributes are directly linked to intangible, internal motivations on the other side, specifically "Social approval?" and "Self-respect?". The implied relationship is that possessing products with these desirable characteristics can lead to or fulfill these psychological needs, suggesting a model where product features serve as a means to achieve social validation and enhance one's sense of self-worth.
